{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Justice Transformation Campaign: The campaign works to end discriminatory and oppressive policies that marginalize Black people and other communities of color, particularly in our education and criminal legal systems. CPD looks to strengthen the power of communities to ensure public safety is defined and resourced through investments in education, health, jobs, and housing, rather than in the trillions currently spent on policing and jails. The campaign supports multijurisdictional campaigns for Black freedom including divest/invest, 94 crime bill repeal, ending criminalization/mass incarceration.

Organizing for Education Justice: Policy priorities include: adequate and equitable investment in transformative public schools, ending the privatization of education, and ending the school-to-prison-and-deportation pipeline





